exportData() - Method in class mvc.ActionBlockData
Export this action block as an encoded data string.
The string always begins with its type, followed by its arguments separated with "_".

Examples:
"Left"
"Goto_X" : X is the line number for jump.
"Loop_X_Y_Z" : Loop (X - Y) times, Z is the line number for jump.
exportData() - Method in class mvc.ActionChainData
Export this action chain as an encoded data string.
The string always begins with "Start" and ends with "End", with each action block separated with ",".

Format: (without whitespace)
"actionBlock1, actionBlock2, ..."

Examples: (without whitespace)
"Start, End"
"Start, Forward, End"
"Start, Loop_2_0_5, Forward, Goto_2, End"
exportData() - Method in class mvc.HighScoreData
Export the high score data to the high score data data file.
exportData() - Method in class mvc.ProgressionData
Export this stage's progression data as an encoded data string.
The string always begins with "Start" and ends with "End", with each action block separated with ",".

Format: (without whitespace)
"stageID, completed, shortestSteps, highestScore, timeSpent, attempts, /, actionChain"
